supervisions.notes: Restitution Hearing scheduled in Br 6 on 12-30-2015 @ 2:00 pm.

miscConds.notes: Costs due within the first 4 years of probation.

The Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - no alcohol or drugs unless prescribed by a physician.  The Defendant is to obtain and maintain full time employment and/or educational programming as recommended.  The Defendant is to have no contact with all businesses involved in crimes from this file and 15CM448.  The Defendant is not to go into any bars, taverns or businesses where the primary purpose is to sell alcohol. (Can be in a restaurant but not the bar area.)  The Defendant is not to have any alcohol or illicit drugs on the premises where he resides.  The Defendant is to participate in and complete the Outagamie County Drug Treatment Court Program.  The Defendant is not to have contact with any drug users or drug dealers.  Upon petition to the Court and a good report from the Drug Treatment Program, Court will consider stay of some of the jail time.  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due, and/or other collection means, such as income assignment will be issued.
**12-30-2015 - Deft agrees to amount of restitution.  Court sets restitution amount at $1362.45 plus $136.24 surcharge.

timeConds.notes:
Consecutive to sentence now serving.  Work release granted for work, school, treatment and treatment court.  12 days credit.

**12-18-2015 - Court amends judgment.  9 months jail is to be in lock-up.

**03-04-2016 - Court amends judgment.  Huber granted for enrollment at Fox Valley Tech, to participate in Drug Court, and treatment.

judgments.action: Guilty Due to No Contest Plea

supervisions.notes: Counts 1, 2 & 3 are consecutive to each other but concurrent to Winnebago County 15CF461.

superMiscConds.notes:
The Defendant is to attend the Drug Victim Impact Panel one time per year. The Defendant is to undergo a mental health assessment and comply with any recommended treatment/counseling.  The Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - no alcohol or drugs unless prescribed by a physician.  The Defendant is not to associate with any drug users or drug dealers.  The Defendant is to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis, unless already provided.  The Defendant is not to go into any bars, taverns or businesses where the primary purpose is to sell alcohol.  The Defendant is to reapply to drug court within 30 days of being released to extended supervision.  The Defendant is to apply for Vivatrol program within 30 days of being released to extended supervision.  The Defendant is to find an AODA sponsor within 6 months of being released to extended supervision.  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due, and/or other collection means, such as income assignment will be issued.

**06-20-2019 - Court amends judgment.  Defendant is to apply to drug court within 6 months of being released to extended supervision.
